 Indian Railways Act, 1890 Ss. 26 and 41-Complaint in respect of past dues cannot be made under s. 41 before Railway Rates Tribunal--In such cages. v. 26 of Act is not a bar to a suit in civil court and question of reasonableness of charges can be gone into by civil court.
 
